sections.Biography:
===Background===
Aerion was a Prince of the [[House Targaryen|Targaryen dynasty]]. His father was King [[Maekar I Targaryen]]. He was the older brother of [[Aemon Targaryen|Aemon]] and [[Aegon V Targaryen|Aegon Targaryen]], who would ascend to [[Iron Throne]] as Aegon V.

Aerion killed himself by drinking [[wildfire]], believing it would transmute him into a [[dragon]].&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Alchemists' Guild (Histories &amp; Lore)]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

===[[Season 3]]===

Touring the [[Great Sept of Baelor]] in [[King's Landing]], King [[Joffrey Baratheon]] points out to [[Margaery Tyrell]] the urn containing what little remains of â&euro;&lsaquo;Aerion Brightflame. He briefly explains who he was and the manner of his death.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[And Now His Watch is Ended]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;
